						               													<description>Hoplite is a game of tactics for 2 players, using 18 identical cards as battle units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Defend, Attack, and Capture the enemy&amp;rsquo;s units to gain dominance over the battlefield!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player controls a phalanx of hoplite soldiers.&amp;#10;Your objective is to kill or capture enemy soldiers until your opponent is unable to make a move.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The cards are laid out on the table in a &amp;lsquo;basketweave&amp;rsquo; pattern, each representing a soldier on the battlefield. Soldiers move by rotating on a corner that is touching an adjacent card; either rotating 90 degrees to touch another card, or if it is on a corner, rotating 180 degrees to align to the new edge. Each player makes two moves on their turn, which can be to move two soldiers, or the same soldier twice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Soldiers have three possible effects when aligned against an enemy card in certain orientations:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;    Attack: remove the enemy from play&amp;#10;    Defend: block an Attack&amp;#10;    Capture: flip an enemy card over so that it joins your side&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By attacking and removing soldiers from play, and capturing enemy cards, you can gain a dominant position and isolate your opponent&amp;rsquo;s cards so that they are unable to move. When they have no possible moves to make, you have won the battle!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
